# github_note
A} basic CLI commands
1. to list all files or folder in a folder:   ls
2. make a new folder:   mkdir folder_name
3. go iside a folder:   cd folder_name
5. to delet a whole non_empty directory/folder:  rm directory_name -rf
5. write a file in git bash vim :   vim file_name
    [1. use insert key to enable the writing mode in any file
     2. them after finishing edits, press the left-right arrow key to disable the writing mode and then write  :x to exit out ]
6. copy + paste in CLI : [use the insert key to paste in Cli or highlight the statement then right click and copy that statement and then right-click on CLI shows the        options.]
